Marc Haddad

Vice - President, Student Government| Co-Founder at Fourty-Two

Marc is a senior at the University of Rochester majoring in Mechanical Engineering. He came to the US from Lebanon 3 years ago, and some of the first people he met here were Sharfuz (unfortunately) and Sidhant. He’s currently the VP of the Student Body, the outgoing president of Meliora Launchpad, and the Mechanical Team Lead for Engineering World Health. He’s heavily involved in the worlds of politics, entrepreneurship, and music. In his free time, Marc likes to play and record music.

Zak Niazi

Founder and Chief Executive Officer at Circle Optics

A graduate of the Institute of Optics at the University of Rochester, Niazi has a history of developing optical innovations including the world’s thinnest scanning fiber endoscope for Harvard Medical School, the first system that quantitatively assesses aberrations in protective eyewear and has experience as an entrepreneur in mobile apps.

Ian Gauger

Chief Operating Officer at Circle Optics

A former Architect, Gauger attended graduate school at the Golisano Institute of Sustainability at the Rochester Institute of Technology and undergraduate at the University of Rochester. He has a background in project and personnel management. To date, he has overseen projects in the Rochester area totaling in the millions of dollars.

Bryan Hiransomboon

Business Technology Consultant, Apple

Bryan Hiransomboon is currently behind these scenes over at Apple TV+ bringing his strategy, skill with technology, and creativity to the world of streaming services. A previously "average" non-target student found his own way of being competitive and broke into the management consulting industry at Deloitte Consulting. Now that he got his foot in the door, he's holding the door by helping others at his alma mater of California State University Northridge and other non-target schools do the same.

Aditya Agashe

Product Manager, Microsoft

Aditya Agashe is a prominent Product Manager and the Author of the bestselling technology strategy book, Swipe to Unlock. He has been featured in the Wall Street Journal, Forbes, Business Insider, Inc. and more. He works on Azure cloud growth team to build hyper-converged and hybrid features that help customers adopt cloud technologies. He is the host of Product Alliance, and has previously managed product and engineering teams as the founder of Belle Applications and Head of Product at Speare.

Parth Detroja

Product Manager, Facebook

Parth Detroja is a distinguished Product Manager and the Author of the bestselling technology strategy book, Swipe to Unlock. He has been featured in the Wall Street Journal, Forbes, Business Insider, Inc. and more. Parth is currently a Product Manager at Facebook where he leads social music product efforts such as adding music to stories on Facebook and Instagram. He has previously worked product management and growth roles at other top tech companies including Microsoft, Amazon, and IBM

Joe Testani

Executive Director, Greene Center

If you are a student at University of Rochester, you will see a smiling approachable face every now and then on campus, especially at Career Center events. That’s none other than Joe Testani, the Assistant Dean & Executive Director of Gwen M. Greene Center for Career Education + Connections of the University of Rochester. He has spent a good portion of his career advocating for students and the value of career education within higher education and, more recently, the future of work and how our communities will be impacted by future generations of workers. He believes career education can serve as a nexus for an ecosystem that includes students, universities + colleges, our communities (local, regional and international), and those that seek to hire talent. He leads a team of 22 staff in a re-envisioned effort to serve students and prepare UR for the Future of Work.

Anisha Khosla

Data & Analytics Consultant at EY

Anisha Khosla is a Consultant in the Data & Analytics practice of Ernst & Young LLP in New York City. Since graduating from the University of Rochester in 2018 with a degree in Biomedical Engineering, Anisha has been working to tackle large scale, unstructured problems through the lens of data in the Financial Services sector. Her professional experiences range across data strategy, data visualization, data quality, and change management, with former internship experiences in the healthcare incubation and global consulting spaces. Outside of work, Anisha remains heavily involved with education equality initiatives through organizations such as She’s The First and Minds Matter – a cause she first grew passionate about during her time at Rochester.

Harshul Batra

Analyst at Goldman Sachs

Harshul is an Analyst at Goldman Sachs in their treasury services and operations department. Most of his work involves learning about the operations and strategy, focusing on improving them as he goes about them. Prior to his work at GS, he used to work primarily in buyside advisory, working with PE firms, Strategic Acquirers and Executives. He studied Financial Economics with a minor in Mathematics and Legal Studies at the University of Rochester.

Evis Drenova

Product Manager at TrueData

After graduating from the University of Massachusetts, Amherst with a BS in Pre-Med/Biology and a minor in Computer Science, Evis started his career in Enterprise Software Sales at Experian Data Quality in Boston and then at Oracle in San Francisco. Evis then transitioned into Management Consulting at IBM where he helped F500 companies develop and implement IT systems strategies. After six years of enterprise software experience, Evis decided to attend The University of Chicago Booth School of Business to pursue an MBA in the Evening MBA program and transitioned into the early-stage startup world at TrueData where was responsible for Product Development.

Daniel Munoz

Software Engineering intern at Autodesk

Daniel is a Computer Science major at the University of Rochester graduating in 2021. At the university he is the president of the Society of Hispanic Professional Engineers (SHPE) club as well as a tutor. He was born and raised in Mexico, the cards that life dealt him led him to only be raised by his grandparents from a very young age. However, resilience and a growth mindset have aided him in conquering the challenges that life throws around and develop a mindset to succeed in the face of adversity. He’s been involved with a student led startup since his first year, research with the medical center, and is now interning as a Software Engineer for Autodesk. In his free time he enjoys to go on long bike rides and listen to audiobooks or practice different forms of dancing such as shuffling, electroswing or breakdancing!

Azfar Merchant

Investment Banking Analyst @ Fairmount Partners

Azfar is currently an investment banking analyst at Fairmount Partners, specializing in mergers & acquisitions. Prior to joining Fairmount, Azfar worked as a strategy consultant in the Financial Services practice at EY in New York where he focused in derivative valuation and retail banking. He received his B.S. in Business with a concentration in Finance. In his spare time, he plays tennis and basketball.

Beatriz Gil

Business Analyst @ Deloitte

Beatriz is a University of Rochester ’19 graduate who is currently working in consulting as a Business Analyst at Deloitte. She is an international student from Spain who wanted to make the most out of her college experience in the US. Hell yeah she did! She decorated her college experience with excellence in academia, research, & campus involvement. She was an Economics and Political Science double major with a double minor in Chinese and International Relations , completed an honors thesis, and was heavily involved with leadership roles in Student Government. Most notably, she made an everlasting contribution to the UR community through extended leadership as a Senator, and in her senior year, as the President of the UR Student Government. If you were a student at UR while she was in college, you definitely saw her smiling face on campus and she had a positive impact in your college experience in some way. She is an awesome person, can rock out to Spanish music better than anyone else, and we are all convinced by now that she is the embodiment of Meliora.

Grace Czechowski

Executive Search Consultant @ Adecco Search

Grace is an Executive search consultant and a Community Champion. She used her leadership skills to navigate new industries, new roles, and new goals. Beginning in aerospace and defense manufacturing, she sought out more personally meaningful opportunities as part of a nonprofit team that helped middle and high school students start their own businesses. Ultimately, she found her passion aligned best with human resources where she could blend her industry knowledge with her desire to help others. She has a wealth of experience and industry knowledge of the recruitment world.

Lauren Lindsey

Senior at Loyola Marymount University

Lauren is a rising senior at Loyola Marymount University, with a major in Computer Science and a minor in Business Administration. On campus, she serves as President to the LMU chapter the the Society Women Engineers. She spent her whole life growing up in the Silicon Valley of the Bay Area, only to find herself there again as an intern at Google. After two summers interning at Google, she accepted an offer to be a Software Engineering Intern at the Walt Disney company, which ended up being cancelled due to COVID-19. Luckily, she is now spending her summer as a Software Engineering intern at SAP!

Azmayeen Rhythm

Solutions Engineer at Ring Central

Rhythm graduated from the University of Rochester in 2019 with a double major in Computer Science and Economics. He came to the United States 5 years ago for college. During the past 5 years he studied abroad in the United Kingdom and Hong Kong. Having lived in different cities around the world taught him how to adapt in new, unknown and sometimes even unwanted situations. Currently He is living in Denver, CO among the Rocky Mountains and working as an Associate Solutions Engineer at RingCentral, Inc. In his free time, he like to play the guitar and explore the Rocky mountains surrounding Denver.

Evan Basta

Sales Engineer at Cisco

Unlike Sharfuz & Sid, Evan didn't fail a class, he failed multiple. He also graduated from U Rochester (they so didn't meet each other at school) where he was at a music school first for some reason before switching to CSC. He started his own venture at school where he fixed people's computers, rode a Harley Davidson and ate too much Chipotle(update:he still does). He didn't want to force himself just to be a software engineer(unlike many) and crafted his career as a Sales Engineer at Cisco. Unlike convention, it took him 6 years to finish college, but unlike many he hacked his way to finding his passion and what he is good at.

Aliye Gallagher

Digital Strategy Advisor

Aliye graduated from the University of Rochester in 2019 with an interdepartmental degree in Digital Communications: Theory, Analysis, Practice. She continued on to California, joining 16 others in the first cohort of Experience Lab at UC Berkeley. Aliye is a strong advocate for alternative educational paths, experiential learning (clearly), and making it up as you go along. She founded and runs a photo and video business for the past six years, which has now expanded into a digital strategy, web design and development, and many forms of the digital art firm.
